OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1784654323
OL,3,COmagh Inquiry Chair urged to keep
OL,4,C'public accountability' in mind
OL,6,FThe chairman of the inquiry into the
OL,7,FOmagh bombing has been urged to keep
OL,8,F"public accountability" in mind as
OL,9,Flegal arguments were heard in relation
OL,10,Fto the anonymity of former police
OL,11,Fofficers.
OL,13,FA barrister for the family of a woman
OL,14,Fkilled in the 1998 attack said the
OL,15,Fpublic would "wonder what has been the
OL,16,Fpurpose of the whole exercise" if the
OL,17,Finquiry cannot address "what was known
OL,18,Fand what wasn't known" by state bodies.
OL,20,FThe Real IRA bombing killed 29 people,
OL,21,Fincluding the mother of unborn twins.
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@WO]wD@NOUxD@^O]yD@XOUzD@VO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/15
